{
  "stem": "833.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was a-- but a very peculiar night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you-- I would recommend that you read Bruno Bettelheim's description of that night, because he does a phenomenal job on the-- towards the last hours, how they simply start integrate-- disintegrated.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How-- how there was a kind of hilarity that we created-- that even the SS-- something had completely changed during that time-- how people just said, OK, I'm going to die.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm dying.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- so what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was-- it was a peculiar-- but as I said, when I read it-- actually, Bruno told me again about it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the best description of what-- of the spirit that it created.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Something entirely different than what it-- could be expected.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was really terrible, but again, I learned something, which I would have never learned otherwise.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "How one can control oneself-- and do things oneself that one didn't know one could do-- control one's blood-- blood circulation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "How'd you do that?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just by not stopping to move for one second any part of your body, so that you can see-- not see it from the outside, but that you still do it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's what I did for the 19 hours.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Everybody can do it, if you have the goal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, I was afraid about my hands, because I-- for a great part, I lived by my hands-- if they are really-- become useless, as many of them became-- so I-- I thought anyway I'm going to-- I'm going to try to not to stop the-- the movement that gave me-- gave me the possibility of having the blood circulation.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't get any frostbite, either.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother did, very heavy.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
